summary: Back on track. I finally got most of the functionality back which was lost in the transition from BLE Central to Bluetooth LE. I...
caption:
Back on track. I finally got most of the functionality back which was lost in the transition from BLE Central to Bluetooth LE. I spare the details. Now on to the making. Today I added two new buttons which essentially verify that I know the service UUID and characteristic ID’s of the Light Blue Bean. Really not sure why the Bluetooth LE plugin was designed that way. I’m just glad it is working.

Also I finally got my github repo up to date: https://github.com/samsadtler/100days
